    FILE_ID                   VARCHAR,
    FILE_SIZE                 NUMBER,
    CONTENT_SHA256            VARCHAR,
    STAGED_FILE_PATH          VARCHAR,
    WEB_URL                   VARCHAR
);

properties.SQL:
delete from docs_groups
where doc_id = '${openflow.doc_id}'
INSERT INTO DOCS_PERMS SELECT '${openflow.doc_id}', PARSE_JSON(${user.ids}), PARSE_JSON(${user.emails})

INSERT INTO DOCS_GROUPS (DOC_ID, GROUP_ID)
SELECT 
    '${openflow.doc_id}' AS DOC_ID,
    value::string       AS GROUP_ID
FROM TABLE(
      FLATTEN(INPUT => PARSE_JSON('${group.ids}'))
) f
;

INSERT INTO DOCS_GROUPS (DOC_ID, GROUP_ID)
SELECT 
    '${openflow.doc_id}' AS DOC_ID,
    value::string       AS GROUP_ID
FROM TABLE(
      FLATTEN(INPUT => PARSE_JSON('${group.ids}'))
) f
;

INSERT INTO PERMS_GROUPS (GROUP_ID, USER_IDS, USER_EMAILS, METADATA)
SELECT
    s.GROUP_ID,
    ARRAY_CONSTRUCT()    AS USER_IDS,
    ARRAY_CONSTRUCT()    AS USER_EMAILS,
    OBJECT_CONSTRUCT()   AS METADATA
FROM (
    -- Flatten the JSON array so each element becomes a separate row
    SELECT value::string AS GROUP_ID
    FROM TABLE(
        FLATTEN(INPUT => PARSE_JSON('${group.ids}'))
    )
) AS s
LEFT JOIN PERMS_GROUPS p
    ON p.GROUP_ID = s.GROUP_ID
WHERE p.GROUP_ID IS NULL;
INSERT INTO DOCS_PERMS SELECT '${openflow.doc_id}', PARSE_JSON(${user.ids}), PARSE_JSON(${user.emails})

INSERT INTO PERMS_GROUPS (GROUP_ID, USER_IDS, USER_EMAILS, METADATA)
SELECT
    s.GROUP_ID,
    ARRAY_CONSTRUCT()    AS USER_IDS,
    ARRAY_CONSTRUCT()    AS USER_EMAILS,
    OBJECT_CONSTRUCT()   AS METADATA
FROM (
    -- Flatten the JSON array so each element becomes a separate row
    SELECT value::string AS GROUP_ID
    FROM TABLE(
        FLATTEN(INPUT => PARSE_JSON('${group.ids}'))
    )
) AS s
LEFT JOIN PERMS_GROUPS p
    ON p.GROUP_ID = s.GROUP_ID
WHERE p.GROUP_ID IS NULL;
DELETE FROM DOCS_PERMS WHERE DOC_ID = '${openflow.doc_id}'

MERGE INTO DOC_METADATA AS t
USING (
    SELECT
        '${openflow.doc_id}'                                    AS DOC_ID,
        '${google.drive.created.time:toDate():format('yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss Z')}' AS CREATED_ON,
        '${google.drive.modified.time:toDate():format('yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss Z')}' AS MODIFIED_ON,
        '${source.filename}'                                    AS FILE_NAME,
        '${mime.type}'                                          AS FILE_MIMETYPE,
        '${source.size}'                                        AS FILE_SIZE,
        '${content_SHA-256}'                                    AS CONTENT_SHA256,
        '${snowflake.staged.file.path}'                         AS STAGED_FILE_PATH,
        '${source.url}'                                         AS WEB_URL,
    	'${source.system}' 										AS SOURCE,
		'${source.identifier}'									AS FILE_ID
) AS s
ON (t.DOC_ID = s.DOC_ID)
WHEN MATCHED THEN
    UPDATE SET
        t.CREATED_ON        = s.CREATED_ON,
        t.MODIFIED_ON       = s.MODIFIED_ON,
        t.FILE_NAME         = s.FILE_NAME,
        t.FILE_MIMETYPE     = s.FILE_MIMETYPE,
        t.FILE_SIZE         = s.FILE_SIZE,
        t.CONTENT_SHA256    = s.CONTENT_SHA256,
        t.STAGED_FILE_PATH  = s.STAGED_FILE_PATH,
        t.WEB_URL           = s.WEB_URL,
        t.SOURCE 			= s.SOURCE,
        t.FILE_ID 			= s.FILE_ID
WHEN NOT MATCHED THEN
    INSERT (
        DOC_ID,
        CREATED_ON,
        MODIFIED_ON,
        FILE_NAME,
        FILE_MIMETYPE,
        FILE_SIZE,
        CONTENT_SHA256,
        STAGED_FILE_PATH,
        WEB_URL,
		SOURCE,
		FILE_ID
    )
    VALUES (
        s.DOC_ID,
        s.CREATED_ON,
        s.MODIFIED_ON,
        s.FILE_NAME,
        s.FILE_MIMETYPE,
        s.FILE_SIZE,
        s.CONTENT_SHA256,
        s.STAGED_FILE_PATH,
        s.WEB_URL,
		s.SOURCE,
		s.FILE_ID
    );
REMOVE @#{Destination Stage} PATTERN = '${openflow.stage_pattern}';

properties.SQL Query:
SELECT 
    GROUP_ID,
    METADATA:"etag"::STRING AS ETAG_CURRENT
FROM PERMS_GROUPS
WHERE GROUP_ID IS NOT NULL AND GROUP_ID != ''
GROUP BY 
    GROUP_ID,
    METADATA:"etag"::STRING;

processors.name: Join Listed Google Groups With Groups Saved In Snowflake

properties.SQL:
SELECT 
  original.id,
  original.etag,
  original.email,
  original.name,
  original.directMembersCount,
  original.description,
  enrichment.ETAG_CURRENT
FROM original
INNER JOIN enrichment
  ON original.email = enrichment.GROUP_ID

MERGE INTO PERMS_GROUPS AS target
USING (
    SELECT
        '${google.group.email}' AS GROUP_ID,
        SPLIT('${google.group.member.user.ids}', ',') AS USER_IDS,
        SPLIT('${google.group.member.user.emails}', ',') AS USER_EMAILS,
        OBJECT_CONSTRUCT(
            'etag', '${etag}',
            'google.group.email', '${google.group.email}',
            'google.group.id', '${google.group.id}',
            'google.group.name', '${google.group.name}'
        ) AS METADATA
) AS source
ON target.GROUP_ID = source.GROUP_ID

WHEN MATCHED THEN
    UPDATE SET
        target.USER_IDS = source.USER_IDS,
        target.USER_EMAILS = source.USER_EMAILS,
        target.METADATA = source.METADATA

WHEN NOT MATCHED THEN
    INSERT (
        GROUP_ID,
        METADATA,
        USER_IDS,
        USER_EMAILS
    )
    VALUES (
        source.GROUP_ID,
        source.METADATA,
        source.USER_IDS,
        source.USER_EMAILS
    );

parameters.description:
Specifies file extensions to ingest.  If all file types are desired then select "Set Empty String". The Microsoft based extensions will be mapped to mime types available in Google such as:


application/vnd.google-apps.document -> docx

application/vnd.google-apps.spreadsheet -> xlsx

Note: the flow tries to convert the files to pdf first, if possible. Nonetheless, the filter is applied to the original file extension. 

Limitation: if some of the specified file extensions are not supported by Cortex Parse Document (e.g., *.foobar) then the flow ignores those files, logs a warning message in an event log, and continues processing other files.
parameters.name: File Extensions To Ingest

parameters.description: The Google Workspace Domain that the Google Groups and Drive resides in.
parameters.name: Google Domain

parameters.description: The Google Shared Drive to watch for content and updates
parameters.name: Google Drive ID

parameters.description:
Optionally, the Google Drive folder identifier (human readable folder name) can be set to filter incoming files by. 

When set, only files that are in the provided folder or subfolder will be retrieved. When blank or unset, no folder filtering is applied and all files under the drive are retrieved.
parameters.name: Google Folder Name

parameters.description: Name of the table to store file hashes to determine if content has changed.  This parameter should not generally need to be changed and is case-insensitive. The table created will always be fully capitalized in Snowflake.
parameters.name: Snowflake File Hash Table Name
